  "place_title": "Day 1 (Pickup Day): Drive from Rishikesh to Lohajung",
  "difficulty": "The drive: You drive along mountain roads, through forests. You also get glimpses of the Garhwal mountains in the distance on a clear day.",
  "duration": "Duration: 10-11 hours | Drive distance: 270 km",
  "altitude": "Altitude: 7,550 ft",
  "water_sources": "",
  "description": "Lohajung is the base camp for the Brahmatal trek. A great way to reach here is from Rishikesh.  The drive from Rishikesh to Lohajung is picturesque. You drive through Devprayag, Rudraprayag and Karnaprayag, the confluence of Alakananda with Bhagirathi, Madakini and Pindari rivers respectively. You drive along mountain roads, and through forests. You also get glimpses of the Garhwal mountains in the distance on a clear day.\nOnce you reach Lohajung, you find yourself face to face with the beautiful Nanda Ghunti peak. If you reach before sunset, the colours of the peak will enthral you.\nLohajung is at the centre of 12-15 nearby villages. There are a couple of local stores where you can buy jackets, hand gloves, caps, shoes etc. if need be. However, it is advised that you carry all the required things for the trek beforehand and not rely on these shops. You will have a mobile network in most parts of Lohajung.\nLohajung, as the locals say, is the place where Goddess Parvati had a war (Jung) with the demon, Lohasur. Hence, the name translates to ‘War with Lohasur.’"
}", "categories_to_extract": ["identity", "geography_and_logistics", "difficulty", "fitness", "age_and_group_suitability", "seasonality", "experience_themes", "risks_and_watchouts", "itinerary_profile", "recommendation_profile", "comparison_axes"]}

