  "day": "4",
  "place_title": "Day 4: Trek from Abin Kharak to Tithak via Ali Top",
  "difficulty": "Difficulty: Easy-Moderate. A level walk on an undulating meadow to begin with and gradual descent through the forest section.",
  "duration": "Trek Duration: 5 hours | Trek Distance: 5.7 km",
  "altitude": "Altitude loss: 11,145 ft to 10,515 ft via 11,600 ft",
  "water_sources": "Water sources: Carry sufficient water. You will cross streams intermittently where you can refill your water bottles.",
  "description": "Take some time in the morning to soak in the mesmerizing sight of the undulating meadows of Ali Bugyal. If you are tempted to take off your shoes and allow the feel of the carpet on your toes, just go ahead and do it!\nYou are on the top of a ridge that spreads in every direction. Acres and acres of green meadow scooped out of the mountainside.\nToday's trek is all about exploring Abin Bugyal and reaching Tithak.\nClimb up for about 200 metres from your campsite and you'll come across stone huts. To start off with the best views for the day, climb up the small mound right in front of you. As you reach the top, you’ll see Mt. Chaukhamba standing tall in the distance. There’s no way you’ll miss it — it has a striking, unmistakable shape that sets it apart from every other peak around.\nTake a left and keep walking on the bugyal. On either side of you, the thick forest stretches endlessly — layer after layer of trees. But don’t get pulled in just yet. Keep walking on the undulating meadows ahead. For the next 2 km, it’s just you and these vast open grasslands. You’ve probably never seen meadows this wide, this endless. It almost feels like they go on forever.\nWhen you reach Ali Top, you are at the highest point of the day. Look around at the peaks near and far. You will be taking the same route you came on to go to Tithak. This time, Mt Trishul and Mt Nanda Ghunti stand infront of you. This is one of the most picturesque trail that we have come across. If the weather is on your side, you can effortlessly click some pictures that can be put up on a photo frame.\nWalk for 2 km to reach the shepherd's hut; your starting point. From here, take the ledge on your left and in about 400 metres, you enter the forest.\nWalk slowly through this thick forest for about 2 kilometres to reach your campsite for the day- Tithak. It is a small clearing in the middle of the forest."
}", "categories_to_extract": ["identity", "geography_and_logistics", "difficulty", "fitness", "age_and_group_suitability", "seasonality", "experience_themes", "risks_and_watchouts", "itinerary_profile", "recommendation_profile", "comparison_axes"]}

