{"task": "section_extraction", "schema_version": "v1", "prompt_version": "trek_metadata_v1", "trek_id": "ali-bedni-bugyal-trek", "trek_title": "Ali Bedni Bugyal Trek", "section_id": "ali-bedni-bugyal-trek::faq_group-001", "section_type": "faq_group", "source_field": "faqs[0:5]", "source_url": "https://indiahikes.com/ali-bedni-bugyal-trek", "section_text": "[
  {
    "question": "Where is Ali Bedni Bugyal?",
    "answer": "Ali Bedni Bugyal is an alpine meadow in the state of Uttarakhand. It lies directly North of popular hill stations like Nainital, Kausani, Almora and Gwaldam. You’ll see these meadows at an elevation range of around 10,000 ft – 11,000 ft. These meadows are famous for being beautiful landmarks on the Roopkund trail.\nIt takes two days of climbing to reach Ali and Bedni Bugyal from Lohajung. If you’re approaching Ali and Bedni Bugyal from Didna, it takes slightly longer (a rough distance of 15 km). Being just south of the Nanda Devi Sanctuary, these meadows have striking views of the peaks within the sanctuary — Mt Nanda Ghunti, Mt Trishul, Maiktoli and Mrigthuni. You also see the Chaukhamba massif from these meadows."
  },
  {
    "question": "What does Bugyal mean?",
    "answer": "Bugyal (pronounced boog-yaal) is a Hindi word that refers to alpine pasture lands or alpine meadows that grow above around 10,500 ft and below 13,000 ft. These alpine meadows are always found above the treeline, so they’re vast open lands, usually with great scenic views of the mountains and valleys around them.\nAli Bugyal and Bedni Bugyal are two of the most famous bugyals in our country. Dayara Bugyal and Gidara Bugyal are other examples of bugyals in India."
  },
  {
    "question": "What is the best time for Ali Bedni Bugyal trek?",
    "answer": "Ali Bedni Bugyal trek is open throughout the year except in monsoons. Spring is the best time to do the trek if what you want is clear skies and grand mountain views. Summer will give you lush greenery in the meadows and wildflowers growing in abundance. But the Ali Bedni winter trek is the one with the most beautiful snow cover in the entire country. For more detailed information, please refer to this section."
  },
  {
    "question": "How long is the Ali Bedni Bugyal trek?",
    "answer": "The Ali Bedni Bugyal trek covers around 30 km in 4 days. (6 days including the drive to and from the trek). The altitude ranges from 7,550 ft in Lohajung all the way to 12,550 ft."
  },
  {
    "question": "What is the speciality of Ali Bedni bugyal?",
    "answer": "Ali Bedni Bugyal has the grandest of mountain views among the meadow treks in our country. You witness the majesty of Mt Trishul and Mt Nanda Ghunti throughout the trek. It has vast meadows and rhododendron forests. For a more detailed guide, you can watch these Ali Bedni Bugyal trek reviews by experts.\nembed\nhttps://youtu.be/dl0O6gv28M8?feature=shared\nvideo\n1.0\nWhy We Love The Ali Bedni Bugyal Trek | A Tribute By Indiahikes\nIndiahikes\nhttps://www.youtube.com/@Indiahikes\nYouTube\nhttps://www.youtube.com/\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/dl0O6gv28M8/hqdefault.jpg\n480\n360\n<iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dl0O6gv28M8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen title=\"Why We Love The Ali Bedni Bugyal Trek | A Tribute By Indiahikes\"></iframe>\nembed\nhttps://youtu.be/MhwqaLTbyvQ?feature=shared\nvideo\n1.0\nChalein Ali Bedni Bugyal Dushyant ke Sath | A Journey to Ali Bedni Bugyal | Indiahikes\nIndiahikes\nhttps://www.youtube.com/@Indiahikes\nYouTube\nhttps://www.youtube.com/\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/MhwqaLTbyvQ/hqdefault.jpg\n480\n360\n<iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MhwqaLTbyvQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen title=\"Chalein Ali Bedni Bugyal Dushyant ke Sath | A Journey to Ali Bedni Bugyal | Indiahikes\"></iframe>"
